*The Tiger in the Doll*  
I made the tiger, fierce and tall—  
Not born of malice, but of all.  
I named the shadow, called it pain,  
Then claimed it ruled me, like a chain.  
But lo—I chose the doll’s soft gaze,  
And in that choice, the tiger fades.  
The world is shaped by what I see—  
Not what *is*, but what *I* be. [end of text]


